TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT BCI.RBAT_ID ,substr($$MAX_RPSDM_PERIOD_ID,1,4) RBAT_BILL_YR_DT_override ,substr($$MAX_RPSDM_PERIOD_ID,5,2) RBAT_BILL_QTR_DT_override , BCI.EXTL_SRC_CD , BCI.EXTL_LVL1_ID , BCI.EXTL_LVL2_ID , BCI.EXTL_LVL3_ID , BCI.COPAY_SRC_CD , BCA.MO_CD , BCA.SPCL_DRUG_CD , BCA.USER_DEF_6_CD , BCI.CLM_PMT_CD ,COUNT(*) CLM_CNT ,MDL.CORP_CD ,coalesce(BCA.RISK_CD,' ') RISK_CD ,BCI.EGWP_CLM_CD ,BCI.MED_PYBL_CD FROM VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_APC BCA, VRAP.RCIT_BASE_CLM_INV BCI ,VRAP.TCORP_MODEL_TYP_CD MDL WHERE BCI.NRE_CLM_CD = '0' AND BCI.INV_ELIG_DT between $$MAX_QTR_STRT_DT and $$MAX_QTR_END_DT AND BCA.CLM_GID = BCI.CLM_GID AND BCI.MODEL_TYP_CD =MDL.MODEL_TYP_CD GROUP BY BCI.EXTL_SRC_CD ,substr($$MAX_RPSDM_PERIOD_ID,1,4) ,substr($$MAX_RPSDM_PERIOD_ID,5,2) , BCI.RBAT_ID , BCI.COPAY_SRC_CD , BCI.EXTL_LVL1_ID , BCI.EXTL_LVL2_ID , BCI.EXTL_LVL3_ID , BCA.MO_CD , BCA.USER_DEF_6_CD , BCA.SPCL_DRUG_CD , BCI.CLM_PMT_CD , MDL.CORP_CD ,coalesce(BCA.RISK_CD,' ') ,BCI.EGWP_CLM_CD ,BCI.MED_PYBL_CD ORDER BY BCI.RBAT_ID , BCI.EXTL_SRC_CD , BCI.EXTL_LVL1_ID , BCI.EXTL_LVL2_ID , BCI.EXTL_LVL3_ID , BCI.COPAY_SRC_CD , BCA.MO_CD , BCA.SPCL_DRUG_CD , BCA.USER_DEF_6_CD , BCI.CLM_PMT_CD

SESSION.DESCRIPTION: This session can be used to get date ranges for certain period types. It uses the VRAP.VRCIT_MODEL_PRD_STUS view, and you pass in the CLM_LOCK_CD and APC_STAT_CD values. It puts out the MIN/MAX Quarter period and Monthly periods, along with their associated Start and End dates, based on what values you pass in. Since it builds a Parameter file for use in another session, you also need to pass in the Folder, Workflow, and the Worklet or Session that will be using the new Parameter file.
